(535, '''amal', '\\^lma\\^ ''amal', '\\\\aw-mal''\\\\', 'a primitive root', 'TWOT - 114', 'v', 'languish 14, feeble 1, weak 1', 16, ' 1) to be weak, to droop, to languish, to be exhausted\r\n    1a) (Qal) pass participle (of the heart)\r\n        1a1) to be weak\r\n        1a2) to droop\r\n    1b) (Pulal)\r\n        1b1) to be or grow feeble\r\n        1b2) to languish\r\n'),
