(553, '''amats', '\\^Uma\\^ ''amats', '\\\\aw-mats''\\\\', 'a primitive root', 'TWOT - 117', 'v', 'strengthen 12, courage 9, strong 5, courageous 2, harden 2, speed 2, stronger 2, confirm 1, established 1, fortify 1, increaseth 1, steadfastly minded 1, obstinate 1, prevailed 1', 41, ' 1) to be strong, alert, courageous, brave, stout, bold, solid, hard\r\n    1a) (Qal) to be strong, brave, bold\r\n    1b) (Piel) to strengthen, secure (for oneself), harden (heart),\r\n        make firm, make obstinate, assure\r\n    1c) (Hithpael) to be determined, to make oneself alert, strengthen\r\n        oneself, confirm oneself, persist in, prove superior to\r\n    1d) (Hiphil) to exhibit strength, be strong, feel strong\r\n'),
