(733, '''Arach', '\\^xra\\^ ''Arach', '\\\\aw-rakh''\\\\', 'from \\\\0732\\\\', '', 'n pr m', 'Arah 4', 4, ' Arah = "traveller"\r\n\r\n 1) a man of Asher\r\n 2) the prominent head of a family of returning exiles\r\n 3) another returned exile\r\n'),
