(948, 'buwts', '\\^Uwb\\^ buwts', '\\\\boots\\\\', 'from an unused root (of the same form) meaning to bleach, i.e. (intransitive) be white, Greek \\\\1040\\\\ \\~bussov\\~', 'TWOT - 219', 'n m', 'fine linen 7, white linen 1', 8, ' 1) byssus, a costly, fine white linen cloth made in Egypt\r\n'),
