(954, 'buwsh', '\\^vwb\\^ buwsh', '\\\\boosh\\\\', 'a primitive root', 'TWOT - 222', 'v', 'ashamed 72, confounded 21, shame 9, all 2 (inf. for emphasis), confusion 1, delayed 1, dry 1, long 1, shamed 1', 109, ' 1) to put to shame, be ashamed, be disconcerted, be disappointed\r\n    1a) (Qal)\r\n        1a1) to feel shame\r\n        1a2) to be ashamed, disconcerted, disappointed (by reason of)\r\n    1b) (Piel) to delay (in shame)\r\n    1c) (Hiphil)\r\n        1c1) to put to shame\r\n        1c2) to act shamefully\r\n        1c3) to be ashamed\r\n    1d) (Hithpolel) to be ashamed before one another\r\n'),
