(1288, 'barak', '\\^Krb\\^ barak', '\\\\baw-rak''\\\\', 'a primitive root', 'TWOT - 285', 'v', 'bless 302, salute 5, curse 4, blaspheme 2, blessing 2, praised 2, kneel down 2, congratulate 1, kneel 1, make to kneel 1, misc 8', 330, ' 1) to bless, kneel\r\n    1a) (Qal)\r\n        1a1) to kneel\r\n        1a2) to bless\r\n    1b) (Niphal) to be blessed, bless oneself\r\n    1c) (Piel) to bless\r\n    1d) (Pual) to be blessed, be adored\r\n    1e) (Hiphil) to cause to kneel\r\n    1f) (Hithpael) to bless oneself\r\n 2) (TWOT) to praise, salute, curse\r\n'),
