(1328, 'B@thuw''el', '\\^lawtb\\^ B@thuw''el', '\\\\beth-oo-ale''\\\\', 'apparently from the same as \\\\01326\\\\ and \\\\0410\\\\', '', '', 'Bethuel 10', 10, ' Bethuel = "God destroys" or "man of God" or "dweller in God"\r\n\r\n n pr m\r\n 1) nephew of Abraham, son of Nahor by Milcah, father of Rebekah\r\n\r\n n pr loc\r\n 2) a town of Simeon in the south\r\n'),
