(2186, 'zanach', '\\^xnz\\^ zanach', '\\\\zaw-nakh''\\\\', 'a primitive root meaning to push aside', 'TWOT - 564', 'v', 'cast...off 17, cast away 1, turn...away 1, removed...far off', 20, ' 1) to cast off, reject, spurn\r\n    1a) (Qal) to reject\r\n    1b) (Hiphil) to forcefully reject someone\r\n 2) to stink, emit stench, become odious\r\n    2a) (Hiphil) stink (perfect)\r\n'),
