(2196, 'za`aph', '\\^Pez\\^ za`aph', '\\\\zaw-af''\\\\', 'a primitive root', 'TWOT - 569', 'v', 'wroth 2, sad 1, fretteth 1, worse liking 1', 5, ' 1) to fret, be sad, be wroth, be vexed, be enraged, be out of humour\r\n    1a) (Qal)\r\n        1a1) to be out of humour\r\n        1a2) to be enraged, be angry\r\n 2) (Qal)\r\n    2a) to appear perplexed, appear troubled\r\n    2b) to be sad-looking\r\n'),
