(2734, 'charah', '\\^hrx\\^ charah', '\\\\khaw-raw''\\\\', 'a primitive root [compare \\\\02787\\\\]', 'TWOT - 736', 'v', 'kindled 44, wroth 13, hot 10, angry 9, displease 4, fret 4, incensed 2, burn 1, earnestly 1, grieved 1, very 1', 90, ' 1) to be hot, furious, burn, become angry, be kindled\r\n    1a) (Qal) to burn, kindle (anger)\r\n    1b) (Niphal) to be angry with, be incensed\r\n    1c) (Hiphil) to burn, kindle\r\n    1d) (Hithpael) to heat oneself in vexation\r\n'),
