(3547, 'kahan', '\\^Nhk\\^ kahan', '\\\\kaw-han''\\\\', 'a primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services', 'TWOT - 959', 'v', 'priest''s office 20, decketh 1, office of a priest 1, priest 1', 23, ' 1) to act as a priest, minister in a priest''s office\r\n    1a) (Piel)\r\n        1a1) to minister as a priest, serve as a priest\r\n        1a2) to be or become a priest\r\n        1a3) to play the priest\r\n'),
