(8414, 'tohuw', '\\^wht\\^ tohuw', '\\\\to''-hoo\\\\', 'from an unused root meaning to lie waste', 'TWOT - 2494a', 'n m', 'vain 4, vanity 4, confusion 3, without form 2, wilderness 2, nought 2, nothing 1, empty place 1, waste 1', 20, ' 1) formlessness, confusion, unreality, emptiness\r\n    1a) formlessness (of primeval earth)\r\n        1a1) nothingness, empty space\r\n    1b) that which is empty or unreal (of idols) (fig)\r\n    1c) wasteland, wilderness (of solitary places)\r\n    1d) place of chaos\r\n    1e) vanity\r\n ++++\r\n For a discussion of the Gap Theory, \\\\see topic 8756\\\\.\r\n'),
